THe green Lizard,
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 Ambr. l. 1. c. 6. or Chloorosaura, is called also the Greater; and the Serpent-fighter, (they worstling serpents.) They haunt hote places, as Italy, where coming of many abroad at once presages a sickly time. In summer they bide in trees, and croak like frogs; and have two tails. The figure below shall save a labour to describe them. It is usefull in Phisick; ty it on thirty dayes for neck-swellings, and then change it. Childrens burstings are cured by a bite, then shoot him through with an arrow,Plin. and bloat him. Boyled alive with wine, and given fasting, it helps wheesings, and sod with oyl, face pimples. With tarre, and an old sows grease it takes away tendernesse of Horse-hoofs: It makes the hair black;
